## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of up-to-date data and the variability in state laws regarding voting rights for incarcerated individuals. Additionally, the perspectives included are primarily from U.S.-based sources, which may not fully capture international viewpoints on the issue. Further research could explore the impact of allowing prisoners to vote in countries where this is already permitted.